				\begin{document}$$|y(t)|$$\end{document}. The measured cross-sections are unfolded to both parton level and particle level. Parton-level measurements can be directly compared to theory predictions that use stable top quarks. Particle-level measurements make use of a top-quark proxy which is constructed with the objects used in the fiducial cross-section measurements. At particle level, it is also possible to measure differential cross-sections as a function of the pT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
