The 4FS and the 5FS are explored. The predictions are computed with the CT10 PDF set and include the uncertainty in the scale choice using the method of independent restricted scale variations as described in Sect. 1 and the uncertainty in the PDFs, using the intra-PDF uncertainties of CT10. The predictions based on the 5FS feature strongly reduced scale uncertainties compared to those based on the 4FS. When computing the predictions of σfid\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
